Class AsyncRPC<R extends com.google.protobuf.Message>

  • java.lang.Object
    • co.cookies.sdk.services.AsyncRPC<R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - Request type which is expected to be submitted with this RPC.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    RPCOperation<R>
    @Immutable
@ThreadSafe
public final class AsyncRPC<R extends com.google.protobuf.Message>
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines a convenience wrapper for an asynchronous RPC operation, which can carry with it a timeout and an optional set of call-level context to apply when executed.

    Asynchronous RPCs are non-blocking, meaning an asynchronous call will never block the thread it is issued from, instead returning immediately with a future container for a result value.
